# HTML Commands




## HTML tag commands {#htmltagcmds}


Here is a list of all HTML commands that may be used inside the documentation. Note that although these HTML tags are translated to the proper commands for output formats other than HTML, all attributes of a HTML tag are passed on to the HTML output only (the <code>HREF</code> and <code>NAME</code> attributes for the <code>A</code> tag are the only exception).

<table class="doxyTable">
<tr>
<th align="left">HTML Command</th>
<th align="left">Description</th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td valign="top"><a id="htmltag_A_HREF"></a> <code>&lt;A HREF="..."&gt;</code></td>
<td valign="top">Starts a hyperlink (if supported by the output format).</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td valign="top"><a id="htmltag_A_ID"></a> <code>&lt;A ID="..."&gt;</code></td>
<td valign="top">Starts a named anchor (if supported by the output format).</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td valign="top"><a id="htmltag_A_NAME"></a> <code>&lt;A NAME="..."&gt;</code></td>
<td valign="top">Starts a named anchor (if supported by the output format).</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td valign="top"><a id="htmltag_endA"></a> <code>&lt;/A&gt;</code></td>
<td valign="top">Ends a link or anchor</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td valign="top"><a id="htmltag_B"></a>  <a id="htmltag_endB"></a>  <code>&lt;B&gt;</code> / <code>&lt;/B&gt;</code></td>
<td valign="top">Starts and ends a piece of text displayed in a bold font.</td>
</tr>

<td valign="top">Starts and ends a quotation block.</td>
</tr>
<tr>

Finally we have the HTML style comments.

<ul class="doxyList ">
<li>When using the, Doxygen, special HTML style comments, i.e. <code>&lt;!--! ... --&gt;</code>, it is not seen as comment but as if the <code>...</code> part is just in the documentation. This is useful to specify Doxygen commands inside a markdown file like:

<div class="doxyProgramListing">

<div class="doxyCodeLine"><span class="doxyNoLineNumber">&nbsp;</span><span class="doxyLineContent"><span class="doxyHighlight">&lt;!--! \page pg1 The page --&gt;</span></span></div>

</div>


which will be ignored by regular Markdown processors, but Doxygen will interpret this as if there was written:

<div class="doxyProgramListing">

<div class="doxyCodeLine"><span class="doxyNoLineNumber">&nbsp;</span><span class="doxyLineContent"><span class="doxyHighlight">\page pg1 The page </span></span></div>

</div></li>
<li>To put invisible comments inside comment blocks, the normal HTML style comments can be used:


<pre><code>  /*! &lt;!-- This is a comment with a comment block --&gt; Visible text */
</code></pre>


The part <code>&lt;!-- ... --&gt;</code> will not be shown in the main documentation.</li>
</ul>

Note: It is explicitly forbidden to use 3 dashes before the closing greater than sign. Doxygen won't see that as the closing either and give a warning.
